  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Describe the feature you would like, or briefly summarise the bug and what you did, what you expected to happen, and what actually happens. Sections below)\r\n*Summary*: If user denied access to camera once then next time on scan QR code or Capture an image app crashes.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what you expected to happen.)\r\nThere is popup or a message that lets user to enable camera access or explain how to do this in Settings. App does not crash\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what actually happened.)\r\nApp crashes\r\n### Reproduction\r\n[comment]: # (Describe how we can replicate the bug step by step.)\r\nvideo: https://drive.google.com/open?id=0Bz3t9zSg1wb7MW93RVZPQ1BRcFE\r\n- Open Status (1st time when no permissions were given)\r\n- Open Profile\r\n- Edit Profile\r\n- Tap on Capture\r\n- Don't allow access the camera\r\n- Close Status\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Now there are 2 ways to crash:\r\n- 1. Edit Profile again and tap on Capture -> app crashes\r\n- 2. Open Contacts, add new contact, scan QR -> app crashes\r\n\r\nAnother way (if permissions already given)\r\n- In Settings remove Camera access for Status app\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Edit Profile and tap on Capture -> app crashes OR\r\n- Open Contacts, add new contact, scan QR -> app crashes\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n[comment]: # (Please do your best to fill this out.)\r\n* Status version: 0.9.6 and later (0.9.7d34)\r\n* Operating System: iOS\r\n\r\n#### Logs\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (if on Android please replicate bug whilst running adb logcat)\r\n[StatusIm-2017-05-01-192218.crash.txt](https://github.com/status-im/status-react/files/968395/StatusIm-2017-05-01-192218.crash.txt)\r\n",
